<subSubSection id="C9C6F1F7FF82CE52FF77FF4FDAB23DC2" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF82CE52FF77FF4FDAB23DC2" blockId="15.[136,778,158,531]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF82CE52FF77FF4FDA513C96" bold="true" box="[136,258,158,184]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF82CE52FE82FF4EDAA03C96" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[381,499,158,185]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tarsalis">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF82CE52FE82FF4EDAA03C96" box="[381,499,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">A. tarsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from those of all species, except 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF82CE52FECCFF14DACC3CF1" box="[307,415,197,223]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castelo">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF82CE52FECCFF14DACC3CF1" box="[307,415,197,223]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">A. castelo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FF82CE52FE52FF14DAAF3CF1" box="[429,508,197,223]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="17.[136,235,1115,1139]" captionTargetBox="[158,1417,199,1057]" captionTargetId="figure-364@17.[151,1436,189,1092]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 12. Actinopus castelo sp. nov., male: A–C MPEG 22277: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI-Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated Area. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597263" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597263/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
A–C), by the copulatory bulb without BTA and by the robust embolar base, inserted basally at a right angle (90°); the embolar apex is flattened and expanded, arrow-shaped in dorsal view. They differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF82CE52FE5CFE8ED95C3D56" box="[419,527,350,377]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castelo">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF82CE52FE5CFE8EDAE73D57" box="[419,436,351,377]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF82CE52FE3FFE8FD95C3D56" box="[448,527,350,376]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">castelo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by PAc inconspicuous at prolateral surface, embolus shorter, tegulum wider than in 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF82CE52FF58FE7DDA453DEB" box="[167,278,427,454]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castelo">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF82CE52FF58FE7DDA453DEB" box="[167,278,427,454]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">A. castelo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and PA more conspicuous (
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FF82CE52FDA9FE7AD9C93DEB" box="[598,666,427,453]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[136,235,952,976]" captionTargetBox="[170,1419,201,919]" captionTargetId="figure-21@14.[151,1436,189,929]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Actinopus tarsalis Perty, 1833 (drawings from Miglio et al., 2012), male: A–C MPEG 11717: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; PAc-ProlateralAccessory keel; PI-Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrow: Serrated Area. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597255/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
A–C, see 
<bibRefCitation id="E54DDF8DFF82CE52FF77FE03DA0F3DC2" author="Miglio, L. T. &amp; Lucas, S. M. &amp; Bonaldo, A. B." box="[136,348,466,492]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="275 - 379" refId="ref139626" refString="Miglio, L. T., Lucas, S. M. &amp; Bonaldo, A. B. (2012) On the identity of the type species Actinopus tarsalis (Araneae: Actinopodidae). Zoologia, 29 (4), 275 - 379. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 1984 - 46702012000400009" type="journal article" year="2012">
Miglio 
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF82CE52FF24FE03DA473DC2" box="[219,276,466,492]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">et al.</emphasis>
, 2012
</bibRefCitation>
, figs 1–12).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
